    "F. Synthetic Surface EvaluationWe first explore F (H, V) by evaluating analytical expressions with parameters chosen to match typical database sensitivities.",
    "This lets us visualize:• latency surfaces,• cost-per-query heatmaps,• coordination overhead surfaces, • objective function landscapes.",
    "Figures 2, 3, and others demonstrate these surfaces.",
    "G. Physical Benchmarking InterfaceTo execute controlled experiments, we use:• Kubernetes clusters with HPA+VPA disabled, • a custom autoscaling controller implementing DIAGO-NALSCALE,• Prometheus + Grafana for monitoring, • Locust/YCSB for load generation.",
    "All experiments were repeated five times; error bars reflect standard deviation."
